---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About Khaled Zaky — Senior Director of Agentic AI Platform Engineering at RBC Borealis.">
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
    <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-gray-900 dark:text-white font-serif mb-10">
      About me
    </h1>

    <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-10 mb-12">
      <img
        src="/img/KhaledZaky.jpeg"
        alt="Khaled Zaky"
        class="w-48 h-48 rounded-2xl object-cover shadow-lg shrink-0"
      />
      <div class="prose dark:prose-invert prose-lg">
        <p class="lead">
          Khaled is Senior Director of Agentic AI Platform Engineering at <strong><a href="https://rbcborealis.com">RBC Borealis</a></strong>, leading the engineering vision and delivery of the bank's next-generation agentic AI platform that powers secure, scalable, and intelligent automation across RBC.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="prose dark:prose-invert prose-lg max-w-none">
      <p>
        His work bridges product strategy, platform architecture, and applied AI—enabling teams to build safe, high-impact AI systems that integrate deeply with enterprise infrastructure.
      </p>

      <p>
        Before joining RBC, Khaled was a Senior Product Manager – Technical at <a href="https://aws.amazon.com">Amazon Web Services (AWS)</a>, where he led the product vision for <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/identity/">AWS Identity</a>, driving innovations in multi-factor authentication (MFA), passkeys, and sign-in experiences that strengthened how millions of customers secure access to AWS.
      </p>

      <p>
        During his time at AWS, he was an active member of the <a href="https://fidoalliance.org/">FIDO Alliance</a> and <a href="https://www.w3.org/groups/wg/webauthn/">W3C WebAuthn Working Groups</a>, contributing to global standards for passwordless authentication and online security.
      </p>

      <p>
        He also teaches at <a href="https://www.coursereport.com/blog/learn-from-a-real-product-manager-at-brainstation-khaled-zaky">BrainStation</a>, mentoring future product leaders and helping them apply technical, security, and AI principles to real-world product challenges.
      </p>

      <p>
        At his core, Khaled is driven by a mission to make intelligent and secure systems accessible to everyone—combining usability, trust, and innovation at scale.
      </p>

      <h2>Interests</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Agentic AI platforms</li>
        <li>Identity and authentication</li>
        <li>Cloud and distributed systems</li>
        <li>Product strategy and platform design</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>About the website</h2>

      <h3>This website is for:</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Sharing information <a href="/about">about</a> myself and what I am up to for the curious minds</li>
        <li><a href="/blog">Publishing</a> some of my ideas, learnings and my work</li>
        <li>Practicing new things I'm <a href="https://github.com/kzaky/khaledzaky.com">learning</a> in my spare time on <a href="https://aws.amazon.com">AWS</a> or other platforms and tools</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Technical details:</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Designed and coded on a <a href="http://www.apple.com/macbook-air">Mac</a></li>
        <li>Coded in <a href="https://windsurf.com">Windsurf</a> and <a href="https://code.visualstudio.com">Visual Studio Code</a></li>
        <li>Built with <a href="https://astro.build">Astro</a>, a modern static site generator with <a href="https://tailwindcss.com">Tailwind CSS</a></li>
        <li>Source Code is hosted on <a href="https://github.com">GitHub</a> available <a href="https://github.com/kzaky/khaledzaky.com">here</a></li>
        <li>Deployed with <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/codebuild/">AWS CodeBuild</a> where the site generation happens when I push my code to <a href="https://github.com/kzaky/khaledzaky.com">my GitHub repo</a></li>
        <li>Hosted on <a href="http://aws.amazon.com">AWS</a> using <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/s3/">Amazon S3</a> for object storage</li>
        <li>Presented to you through <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/cloudfront/">Amazon CloudFront</a> for content distribution</li>
        <li>Secured by a SSL/TLS certificate from <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/certificate-manager/">AWS Certificate Manager</a></li>
        <li>Blog posts are researched and drafted with the help of an AI agent powered by <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/bedrock/">Amazon Bedrock</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
